{"questionId":"2675784","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Alvie wants to buy this car. On 1 January 2023, he invested <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>15</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math> in an account that earns <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math> annual interest compounded yearly. He makes no further deposits to, or withdrawals from, the account.</p>\n<p>Alvie wishes to buy this car for its value on 1 January 2028. In addition to the money in his account, he will need an extra <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mi>M</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of the car on 1 January 2028.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24961</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25000</mn></math> (dollars)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2675784","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of the car on 1 January 2028.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.4—Financial apps – compound int, annual depreciation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
